{
  "text": "For detection of the different members of the TOC1 family, plants were maintained in 12-h/12-h light/dark cycles for 6 days before samples were harvested every 4 h during one light/dark cycle. RNA was extracted using the RNeasy Plant Mini Kit according to the manufacturer's recommendations (Qiagen). SuperScript II RNase H \u03ea re-verse transcriptase (Gibco BRL) was used to synthesize the firststrand cDNA with oligo(dT 12-18 ) primer (Gibco BRL) from 1 g of total RNA at 42\u040aC for 50 min. Two microliters of the cDNAs from each time point was combined in one tube, and 1 L of the mixture was used for PCR amplification using specific primers for each member of the TOC1 family [CITATION_1] . Samples were run on 1.2% agarose gels, transferred to nitrocellulose membranes, and subjected to hybridization according to standard protocols.",
